---

Attributes attach to blocks too, as on the heading below.

## Styled heading {.featured #styled}

Per-item classes ride an inline span (`[text]{.class}`); carve-js drops a bare
`{.class}` line under an item, so the span form is what actually emits a class:

- [ ] [needs fixing]{.error}
- [x] [shipped]{.success}

## Extension showcase

Verifies the live-preview hydration: language badge, header caption, tabs,
spoiler, details, mermaid, chart, and math (each should render in preview).

A fenced block carries a language badge and a quoted-header caption bar:

``` php "app/Service.php" [Service]
<?php echo "hi";
```

A code group switches panels on tab click:

::: code-group
``` js [JavaScript]
const x = 1;
```
``` ts [TypeScript]
const x: number = 1;
```
:::

A tab set:

:::: tabs
::: tab [First]
First panel body.
:::
::: tab [Second]
Second panel body.
:::
::::

Inline spoiler blurs until clicked: :spoiler[hidden answer].

::: spoiler "Block spoiler"
The hidden block body.
:::

:::details "Disclosure"
A native details/summary disclosure.
:::

A mermaid diagram:

``` mermaid
graph TD; A[Start] --> B{Choice}; B -->|yes| C[Do it]; B -->|no| D[Skip];
```

A chart:

``` chart
{"type":"bar","data":{"labels":["Q1","Q2","Q3"],"datasets":[{"label":"Sales","data":[12,19,7]}]}}
```

Display math: ``` math `` and inline math $`a^2 + b^2 = c^2`$.

``` math
\int_0^1 x^2 \, dx = \frac{1}{3}
```
